<DocsPage
  title="Package discovery"
  description="Use the curated catalog to find packages worth installing into your repo."
>
  <p>
    The public package catalog is curated rather than scraped. That keeps the initial browsing
    experience useful and avoids presenting arbitrary repositories as installable Nodus packages
    without review.
  </p>

  <p>Use the catalog to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>find starter packages for your adapter stack</li>
    <li>discover rules, skills, and commands by workflow</li>
    <li>jump to the package repository and docs quickly</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Browse the live index at <a href="/packages/">/packages/</a>.</p>
</DocsPage>
